quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to fit the text into the paragraph:
[!raw!]
p {
 width: 300px;
 {0}: {1};
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The word-wrap Property[/h1]

The word-wrap property allows long words to be broken and wrapped into the next line. It takes two values: [b]normal[/b] and [b]break-word[/b]. 

In the example below, the word-wrap property is set to [b]normal[/b].
[b]The CSS:[/b][code format="css" codeId="596"]p {
   width: 210px; 
   height: 100px;
   border: 1px solid #000000;
   [b]word-wrap: normal;[/b]
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2683" width="100%"]
Now let's see what happens when we use this same example and set the word-wrap property to break-word: [code format="css" codeId="597"]p {
   width: 210px; 
   height: 100px;
   border: 1px solid #000000;
   [b]word-wrap: break-word;[/b]
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2684" width="100%"]
[note]When the word-wrap property is set to [b]break-word[/b], the browser breaks a word when it is too long to fit within its container.[/note]
